studyHtml.fullStudyHtml:
↑Higher Eggs Predicts Very Slightly ↑Higher Overall Mood

Overall Mood was generally 0.6% lower following above average Eggs over the previous 14 days.

Predictor User Variable

Eggs

launch Click for more details about the predictor variable.

Outcome User Variable

Overall Mood

launch Click for more details about the user's outcome variable data in this study.

The Relationship for the Average Person

Aggregate Correlation

launch Examination of the likely effects of a predictor variable on an outcome variable on average for the entire population

Abstract

Overall Mood was generally 0% higher than average after a total of 4 serving of Eggs over the previous 14 days.

This data suggests with a HIGH degree of confidence (p=0.377, 95% CI -0.028 to 0.038) that Eggs has a very weakly positive predictive relationship (R=0.0048) with Overall Mood.

The highest quartile of Overall Mood measurements were observed following an average 0.402 serving Eggs per day.

The lowest quartile of Overall Mood measurements were observed following an average 0.421 serving of Eggs per day.

After an onset delay of 30 minutes, Overall Mood is typically 0% lower than average over the 14 days following around 0.421 serving Eggs.

Objective

The objective of this study is to determine the nature of the relationship (if any) between Eggs and Overall Mood. Additionally, we attempt to determine the Eggs (serving) values most likely to produce optimal Overall Mood values.

Participant Instructions

Record your Eggs daily


Record your Overall Mood daily

Design

This study is based on data donated by one participant. Thus, the study design is consistent with an n=1 observational natural experiment.

Data Analysis

Eggs Pre-Processing

Eggs measurement values below 0 serving were assumed erroneous and removed. Eggs measurement values above 40 serving were assumed erroneous and removed. It was assumed that any gaps in Eggs data were unrecorded 0 serving measurement values.

Overall Mood Pre-Processing

Overall Mood measurement values below 1 out of 5 were assumed erroneous and removed. Overall Mood measurement values above 5 out of 5 were assumed erroneous and removed. No missing data filling value was defined for Overall Mood so any gaps in data were just not analyzed instead of assuming zero values for those times.

Predictive Analytics

It was assumed that 30 minutes would pass before a change in Eggs (serving) would produce an observable change in Overall Mood.

It was assumed that Eggs (serving) could produce an observable change in Overall Mood for as much as 14 days after the stimulus event.

Eggs Data Quantity

There are currently 874 raw measurements with 138 changes spanning 879 days from 2015-12-29 to 2018-05-26.

Overall Mood Data Quantity

There are currently 17126 raw measurements with 1666 changes spanning 3419 days from 2012-04-06 to 2021-08-15.

Statistical Significance

Using a two-tailed t-test with alpha = 0.05, it was determined that the change in Overall Mood is not statistically significant at a 95% confidence interval. This suggests that the Eggs value does not have a significant influence on the Overall Mood value.

After treatment, a 0.6% decrease (-0.0165 out of 5) from the mean baseline 2.88 out of 5 was observed. The relative standard deviation at baseline was 10.7%. The observed change was 0.06 times the standard deviation.

A common rule of thumb considers a change greater than twice the baseline standard deviation on two separate pre-post experiments may be considered significant. This occurrence would have only a 5% likelihood of resulting from random fluctuation (a p-value < 0.05).

Data Sources

Eggs (serving) data was primarily collected using QuantiModo. QuantiModo allows you to easily track mood, symptoms, or any outcome you want to optimize in a fraction of a second. You can also import your data from over 30 other apps and devices. QuantiModo then analyzes your data to identify which hidden factors are most likely to be influencing your mood or symptoms.

Overall Mood data was primarily collected using QuantiModo. QuantiModo allows you to easily track mood, symptoms, or any outcome you want to optimize in a fraction of a second. You can also import your data from over 30 other apps and devices. QuantiModo then analyzes your data to identify which hidden factors are most likely to be influencing your mood or symptoms.

Limitations

As with any human experiment, it was impossible to control for all potentially confounding variables. Correlation does not necessarily imply causation. We can never know for sure if one factor is definitely the cause of an outcome. However, lack of correlation definitely implies the lack of a causal relationship. Hence, we can with great confidence rule out non-existent relationships. For instance, if we discover no relationship between mood and an antidepressant this information is just as or even more valuable than the discovery that there is a relationship.

We can also take advantage of several characteristics of time series data from many subjects to infer the likelihood of a causal relationship if we do find a correlational relationship. The criteria for causation are a group of minimal conditions necessary to provide adequate evidence of a causal relationship between an incidence and a possible consequence.

Criteria For Causal Inference

Strength (A.K.A. Effect Size)

A small association does not mean that there is not a causal effect, though the larger the association, the more likely that it is causal. There is a very weakly positive (R = 0.0048) relationship between Eggs Consumption and Overall Mood.

Consistency (A.K.A. Reproducibility)

Consistent findings observed by different persons in different places with different samples strengthens the likelihood of an effect. Furthermore, in accordance with the law of large numbers (LLN), the predictive power and accuracy of these results will continually grow over time. 883 paired data points were used in this analysis. Assuming that the relationship is merely coincidental, as the participant independently modifies their Eggs Consumption values, the observed strength of the relationship will decline until it is below the threshold of significance. To it another way, in the case that we do find a spurious correlation, suggesting that banana intake improves mood for instance, one will likely increase their banana intake. Due to the fact that this correlation is spurious, it is unlikely that you will see a continued and persistent corresponding increase in mood. So over time, the spurious correlation will naturally dissipate.

Specificity

Causation is likely if a very specific population at a specific site and disease with no other likely explanation. The more specific an association between a factor and an effect is, the bigger the probability of a causal relationship.

Temporality

The effect has to occur after the cause (and if there is an expected delay between the cause and expected effect, then the effect must occur after that delay). The confidence in a causal relationship is bolstered by the fact that time-precedence was taken into account in all calculations.

Biological Gradient

Greater exposure should generally lead to greater incidence of the effect. However, in some cases, the mere presence of the factor can trigger the effect. In other cases, an inverse proportion is observed: greater exposure leads to lower incidence.

Plausibility

A plausible bio-chemical mechanism between cause and effect is critical. This is where human brains excel.

Based on our responses so far,

0 humans feel that there is a plausible mechanism of action for a relationship between Eggs Consumption and Overall Mood.

Seems coincidental?
Down Vote ➤  

Coherence

Coherence between epidemiological and laboratory findings increases the likelihood of an effect. It will be very enlightening to aggregate this data with the data from other participants with similar genetic, diseasomic, environmentomic, and demographic profiles.

Experiment

All of human life can be considered a natural experiment. Occasionally, it is possible to appeal to experimental evidence.

Analogy

The effect of similar factors may be considered.

Plausibility

A plausible bio-chemical mechanism between cause and effect is critical. This is where human brains excel. Based on our responses so far, 0 humans feel that there is a plausible mechanism of action and 0 feel that any relationship observed between Eggs Consumption and Overall Mood is coincidental.

studyText.studyObjective: The objective of this study is to determine the nature of the relationship (if any) between Eggs and Overall Mood. Additionally, we attempt to determine the Eggs (serving) values most likely to produce optimal Overall Mood values.

This analysis suggests that higher Eggs (Foods) generally predicts higher Overall Mood (p=0.377, 95% CI -0.028 to 0.038)

Overall Mood is0% higher after around 0.402 serving Eggs.

After an onset delay of 30 minutes, Overall Mood is generally 0% than its average over the 14 days following around 0.421 serving Eggs.

EGGS Data Quantity: There are 874 raw Eggs (serving) measurements. There are 874 Eggs (serving) measurements when you include those derived from tagged duplicate, child or ingredient variables and those derived from zero filling gaps in data. There 138 changes spanning 879 days from 2015-12-29 to 2018-05-26. OVERALL MOOD Data Quantity: There are 17126 raw Overall Mood measurements. There are 17126 Overall Mood measurements when you include those derived from tagged duplicate, child or ingredient variables and those derived from zero filling gaps in data. There 1666 changes spanning 3419 days from 2012-04-06 to 2021-08-15.

The top quartile outcome values are preceded by an average 0.402 serving of Eggs.

The bottom quartile outcome values are preceded by an average 0.421 serving of Eggs.

The Forward Pearson Predictive Coefficient was 0.0048((p=0.377, 95% CI -0.028 to 0.038) , onset delay = 30 minutes, duration of action = 14 days).

The Reverse Pearson Predictive Coefficient was (0.3768941602688, 95% CI -0.033 to 0.033, onset delay = -30 minutes, duration of action = -14 days).

When the Eggs value is closer to 0.402 serving than 0.421 serving, the Overall Mood value which follows is 0 percent higher than its typical value.

When the Eggs value is closer to 0.421 serving than 0.402 serving, the Overall Mood value which follows is generally 0% than its typical value.

Overall Mood is 2.92/5 (2% higher) on average after days with around 2.17 serving Eggs (serving)
